This recipe is nothing less than "WOW" in my opinion. This soup is worthy of serving in a restaurant, at your next dinner party, or with some crusty bread and wine on a cold night. Here's what I did different from the recipe: 1. used low sodium chicken broth instead of water 2. used strips of pancetta (instead of chopped) so I could fish them out before serving 3. omitted the fennel, not available the day i went to the grocery store. You will not regret making this soup. Your family, including young children, will jump up and down and think you're a Super Mom. Enough said.

