What an amazing idea with the pistou!!!, I wish I had had that secret many years ago, changes I had to make due to what was around: broth was 8 cups water with one frozed (Christmas)ham bone, simmered for 2 hours, yeilded 2 cups ham chips, so omitted the need for bacon, added 2 cups chopped red onion, 3 med carrots, julienned with gadget(=2 minutes prep), 2 cups shredded raw coleslaw from bag, rind from Parm,2 chopped potatoes, sprigs thyme and savory, 2 cups chopped green beans, and one jar of homemade canned tomatoes (always worth taking time in fall to can them for amazing soups) and then the pistou, didn't have that much fresh basil around, so used two heaping tsp. pesto from a jar, so no blender, resulted in little chopping and little mess and this soup is the best...wish I had company now!!

