This was a good one for me to try because I usually don't care much for vegetable soups, but this one was pretty good. I didn't have any fennel left from my dinner party the other night so I put in a dash of ground fennel. I also chopped up fresh brussel sprouts in lieu of cabbage since that's what was in the fridge. This recipe allows for variation in veggies because the pancetta (I used bacon) gives so much flavor. I made the mistake of adding the pistou to the leftovers overnight and it overpowered the soup the next day. The next time I will keep them separate until serving for a fresh taste with each serving.

