Rating: 4
My impression about this soup is that what makes it so good is the base and the pisou. I used just what I already had at home to make this, which meant that I left out fennel bulb, turnips, cabbage, squash, potato, lima beans, cheese rind, and canellini. And yes, those are half the ingredients. But I added extra onion, celery, extra carrots, extra green beans, garbanzo beans, added a pinch of fennel seed (to replace the fennel bulb) used purchased pesto with a couple extra cloves of garlic added, and cooked with chicken broth instead of water. Added pesto and salt to tastse. I'm sure it sounds like my version is qualitatively different from the original, but I believe that the main flavor is probably still the same, and that was WONDERFUL. My husband, a vegetable lover, agreed.

